text: Leechia sinuosalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by South in 1901. It is found in China (Shaanxi, Gansu, Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Fujian, Guangdong, Sichuan), Japan and Taiwan. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1901 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Leechia sinuosalis
